<title>UK: Halifax 9-mth oper profit 752 mln stg.</title>
<headline>Halifax 9-mth oper profit 752 mln stg.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-12-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Nine months to October 31, 1996.</p>
<p>			  (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Operating profit	   803.5		vs 1,240.7</p>
<p> Profit before tax	  752		  vs 1,240.7</p>
<p> Profit after tax	   464.6		vs 811.9</p>
<p>NOTE - The comparative figure refers to pro-forma data for the 12 months ended January 31, 1996. The pro-forma figures reflect the combined results for the 12-month period of Halifax and the Leeds Permanent Building Society, which merged on August 1, 1995. The Halifax plans to go public next year.  </p>
<p> Gross mortgage lending   8,321		vs n/a</p>
<p> Net mortgage lending     1,217		vs n/a</p>
<p> Bad debt provision	 83.4		 vs 106.1</p>
